Gauteng Judge President Dunstan Mlambo says he laments the loss of public confidence in the judicial system. Judges coming under attack, courts being used for corruption gains. eNCA's Heidi Giokos has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Judge President Dunstan Mlambo says he laments the loss of public confidence in the judicial system. Some of the concerns raised by the third Chief Justice candidate include, judges coming under attack and the courts being used for corruption gains. READ: JSC to interview nominees for position of Chief Justice Mlambo is vying to become the next Chief Justice. He believes he has what it takes to strengthen the independence of the judiciary.